This paper is about offline handwritten Chinese text recognition, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm that utilizes machine learning techniques such as Gaussian mixture models (GMMs) and deep neural networks (DNNs), which are commonly studied in sub-categories such as cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.IR.
